description:
Bug 3666 - Code Completion Hungry code assist (1GDRYW5)

Under certain circumstances, the code assist feature is consuming too much code. Here is an example:

public class X {
    void bar(X x) {
        baz(x.foo());
    }
    int foo() {
        return 5;
    }
    void baz(int i, int j) {
    }
}

To reproduce this issue, follow these steps:

1. Change the baz call to:
   baz(x.x.foo())
2. Place the cursor after the first "x."
3. Press CtrlSpace to bring up the code assist
4. Type "f" to filter the list
5. Select "foo()"

Expected behavior:

The code assist should only replace the selected portion of code and not consume additional code.
